      <p class="article-subtitle">Where the smoke of copper vats rises from centuries-old cooking houses and crystal formations echo the limestone karsts of central Vietnam, a sugar of profound distinction is born — <em>Tinh Hoa Mía</em>, the essence of Vietnamese sugarcane art.</p>
