      <p class="lead">Before refined white sugar dominated supermarket shelves, Vietnamese households relied on <em>đường phơi</em> — a sun-dried, preservative-free cane sugar crafted through a traditional process passed down through generations. Greenie Vietnam brings this artisanal product to global wholesale, retail, and private label markets with documented quality and flexible packaging.</p>

      <h2>The Geography of Sweetness</h2>
      <p>Quang Ngai province in central Vietnam possesses a unique microclimate shaped by the Truong Son mountain range to the west and the East Sea to the east. This collision of cool mountain air and warm coastal humidity creates a stress environment that forces sugarcane to produce higher concentrations of natural sucrose — up to 18% BRIX at harvest, compared to the global average of 13–15%.</p>

      <blockquote>
        <p><strong>The Copper Vat Tradition:</strong> Each copper vat has been in continuous use for over 40 years, seasoned by thousands of batches. The copper linings have developed a natural patina that subtly influences crystallization — a quality modern stainless steel cannot replicate.</p>
      </blockquote>

      <p>Our partner artisans are fourth-generation <em>nghệ nhân nấu đường</em> — sugar alchemists — whose sensory knowledge of crystallization cannot be taught in any institution. They can determine the precise moment of peak crystallization by sound alone: the shift in bubbling pitch when sucrose concentration reaches the critical threshold.</p>

      <blockquote>
        <p>We don't sell sugar — we share terroir.</p>
        <footer>— Greenie Vietnam Artisan Products</footer>
      </blockquote>

      <h2 class="accent-green">Flavor Profile</h2>
      <p>Each batch follows a protocol that has remained virtually unchanged for over a century.</p>

