      <p>The reduction process is the soul of Tinh Hoa Mía. In the cool pre-dawn hours, freshly pressed cane juice is poured into copper vats that have been in continuous use for over four decades. Each vat carries a natural patina — a living seasoning built from thousands of batches — that subtly influences the caramelization chemistry.</p>

      <p>Over 8 hours of gentle, controlled boiling, the juice transforms. The artisans — <em>nghệ nhân nấu đường</em> — monitor not by thermometer but by sound and sight. They recognize the exact moment when the bubbling pitch shifts and the syrup reaches the critical sucrose concentration. This sensory knowledge, passed down through four generations, cannot be replicated by any machine.</p>

      <p>After reduction, the concentrated syrup is poured into bamboo molds and placed under the tropical sun for final crystallization. The solar finish is crucial — it produces golden crystals with a distinct mineral complexity and a moisture content of ≤4%, ensuring long shelf stability without preservatives.</p>

